Program: The Forum
Title: Anger
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03hwrh5
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 17 Feb 2016
Feeling angry has always been an integral part of our nature, an instant response to being insulted, restrained or threatened. But is modern life making us angrier? And what goes on in our brain when we ‘snap’? Bridget Kendall talks to psychologist Raymond Chip Tafrate, historian of emotions Tiffany Watt Smith and neurobiologist R. Douglas Fields. Photo: Two angry people yell at each other (Credit: Corbis) Show less